"{\"uid\": \"newsus.cgtn.com-news-2024-08-05-Day-9-of-Olympics-is-One-to-Remember-for-China-s-Men-s-Swimming-1vO6qtJb2M0-p.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Our Privacy Statement & Cookie Policy  By continuing to browse our site you agree to our use of cookies, revised Privacy Policy and Terms of Use.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 145, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You can change your cookie settings through your browser.\", \"from\": 146, \"to\": 203, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"CGTN  Copied  The People\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Republic of China is tied with the U.S. on the gold medal leaderboard as of Sunday, August 4.\", \"from\": 205, \"to\": 327, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Team China won a number of competitions on day 9 of the Paris Olympics, including the men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s 100-meter freestyle medley relay, which saw the end of the U.S.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099 40-year-long reign over the race.\", \"from\": 328, \"to\": 522, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 328, \"end\": 338, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_at_the_2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999999986358, \"rank\": 1.030177171882329e-12, \"text\": \"Team China\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_at_the_2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_at_the_2008_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 442, \"end\": 448, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Medley_swimming\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9247390360096565e-26, \"text\": \"medley\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Medley_swimming\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Medley_swimming\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The thrilling heat saw a photo finish, with the Chinese team\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s anchor and 100-meter freestyle gold medalist, Pan Zhanle, overtaking the U.S. swimmer in the final leg of the race to bring home the gold for China.\", \"from\": 524, \"to\": 737, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 572, \"end\": 579, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9936080877628125, \"rank\": 0.0028034936606489507, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 731, \"end\": 736, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9998348911626668, \"rank\": 0.0001512321382008066, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"China\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s team also won bronze in the 100-meter freestyle medley relay in a competition that saw the U.S. break the world record to win gold.\", \"from\": 739, \"to\": 890, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Not far behind the U.S. and China was the French team, who took home bronze and nearly won the competition themselves.\", \"from\": 892, \"to\": 1010, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 920, \"end\": 925, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9998348911626668, \"rank\": 0.0001512321382008066, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 934, \"end\": 940, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.6113687761340588, \"rank\": 0.634810021327901, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Team China also continued their dominance in table tennis after Fan Zhendong won gold in the men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s singles competition, joining fellow compatriot, Chen Meng, from the women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s team to win the Olympic competition.\", \"from\": 1012, \"to\": 1227, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1012, \"end\": 1022, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_at_the_2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999999986358, \"rank\": 1.030177171882329e-12, \"text\": \"Team China\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_at_the_2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_at_the_2008_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1076, \"end\": 1088, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fan_Zhendong\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Fan Zhendong\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13382519\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fan_Zhendong\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fan_Zhendong\"}, {\"begin\": 1161, \"end\": 1170, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chen_Meng\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Chen Meng\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13382519\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chen_Meng\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chen_Meng\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Zhengdong cemented his legacy as one of the greatest table tennis players in Olympic history after winning the singles competition, joining fellow Chinese greats like Ma Long, Zhang Like and Wang Hao to win multiple medals.\", \"from\": 1229, \"to\": 1452, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1376, \"end\": 1383, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9936080877628125, \"rank\": 0.0028034936606489507, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 1396, \"end\": 1403, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ma_Long\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ma Long\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13382519\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ma_Long\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ma_Long\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s artistic gymnastics, China\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Liu Yang won the gold in the rings competition, with fellow countryman You Jingyuan winning silver.\", \"from\": 1454, \"to\": 1595, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1496, \"end\": 1504, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emperor_Ming_of_Han\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.534571450968369e-20, \"text\": \"Liu Yang\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emperor_Ming_of_Han\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emperor_Ming_of_Han\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Chinese men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s and women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s gymnastics team has now won six medals, including one gold and four silvers.\", \"from\": 1597, \"to\": 1707, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"China\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s boxing team is hoping to secure their own golds in the coming days, following 75kg boxer Li Qian advanced to the semifinal, guaranteeing herself an Olympic medal.\", \"from\": 1709, \"to\": 1891, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In addition to Qian, China\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Chang Yuan will compete for the 63.5kg gold medal in women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s boxing after advancing to the finals on Sunday, August 4.\", \"from\": 1893, \"to\": 2044, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1908, \"end\": 1912, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Qian_River\", \"score\": 0.9711512749775008, \"rank\": 0.029705696492252177, \"text\": \"Qian\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Qian_River\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Qian_River\"}, {\"begin\": 1924, \"end\": 1934, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chang_Yuan\", \"score\": 0.9998440536556209, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Chang Yuan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chang_Yuan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chang_Yuan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s olympic boxing will also have its first ever medalist from the Refugee Olympic Team after boxer Djankeu Ngamba reached the 75kg weight\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s semifinals - she is guaranteed at least a bronze medal.\", \"from\": 2046, \"to\": 2250, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2119, \"end\": 2139, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/IOC_Refugee_Olympic_Team_at_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9902603356880152, \"rank\": 0.009835458371872488, \"text\": \"Refugee Olympic Team\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/IOC_Refugee_Olympic_Team_at_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/IOC_Refugee_Olympic_Team_at_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 2160, \"end\": 2166, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ngambaa\", \"score\": 0.9999190014912164, \"rank\": 8.089032743650668e-05, \"text\": \"Ngamba\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ngambaa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ngambaa\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s tennis, the young Spaniard, Carlos Alcaraz, faced off against the legendary Novak Djokovic of Serbia, in what was a rematch of the 2024 Wimbledon championship.\", \"from\": 2252, \"to\": 2422, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2291, \"end\": 2305, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlos_Alcaraz\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Carlos Alcaraz\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlos_Alcaraz\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlos_Alcaraz\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, this time around, it was Djokovic who won the tournament, bringing home gold for Serbia.\", \"from\": 2424, \"to\": 2521, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2458, \"end\": 2466, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"score\": 0.9999998863170341, \"rank\": 1.1368303267217567e-07, \"text\": \"Djokovic\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\"}, {\"begin\": 2514, \"end\": 2520, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia\", \"score\": 0.9999268445015209, \"rank\": 6.853043257435812e-05, \"text\": \"Serbia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Finally, in the highly anticipated men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s 100 meter dash, the U.S.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099 Noah Lyles edged out Jamaica\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Kishane Thompson to win gold by less than one-one hundredth of a second.\", \"from\": 2523, \"to\": 2699, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2594, \"end\": 2604, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Noah Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For more, check out our exclusive content onCGTN Nowand subscribe to our weekly newsletter,The China Report.\", \"from\": 2701, \"to\": 2809, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2796, \"end\": 2808, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_Report\", \"score\": 0.9999999965070856, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"China Report\", \"types\": [\"Q737498\", \"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_Report\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_Report\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466\", \"from\": 2811, \"to\": 3071, \"entities\": []}]}"